2 HOUSE BILL 1212
1 (ii) any other stakeholder considered necessary by the Secretary of
2 Agriculture and the Secretary of Natural Resources.
3 (c) The Department of Agriculture and the Department of Natural Resources
4 jointly shall provide staff for the workgroup.
5 (d) On or before December 1, 2026, the Secretary of Agriculture and the Secretary
6 of Natural Resources jointly shall report the findings of the workgroup convened under this
7 section and any recommendations of the workgroup, including recommendations for
8 legislation, to the Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government
9 Article, the Senate Committee on Education, Energy, and the Environment and the House
10 Environment and Transportation Committee.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
12 1, 2026. It shall remain effective for a period of 1 year and 1 month and, at the end of June
13 30, 2027, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall be
14 abrogated and of no further force and effect

